<TITLE> Babul and family get bail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 17 (bdnews24.com) -- A Dhaka court Monday granted bail to Jamuna Group chairman Nurul Islam Babul and his family members after they surrendered in a case filed by the Office of the Registrar of Joint Stock Companies and Firms. Magistrate Md Emran Hossain Chowdhury of the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court for Dhaka also granted bail to some other officials of Jamuna Group and its seven associated organisations after they turned themselves in to the court. The magistrate set the accused a bail bond of Tk 10,000 each. Those granted bail were Babul, wife advocate Salma Islam, their three daughters Shariat Tasrin, Sabiha Naznin and Sumaiya Islam, Babul's three brothers Tazul Islam, Md Sohrab Uddin and Mizanur Rahman and chartered accountant Nurul Islam. All the accused are the top officials of the seven companies. Another accused in the case, Babul's son Shamim Islam, could not appear in court because of his illness, lawyers said. Advocate Md Abdul Bari, who took part in the bail hearing on behalf of the accused, said the allegations, brought against them were "bailable". Abdul Mannan of the Office of the Registrar of Joint Stock Companies and Firms filed seven cases against as many associate companies with the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court for Dhaka on Dec 19, last year on charges of discrepancies in financial statements and other documents submitted on behalf of the companies. In the seven separate cases, filed on charges of breaching the Companies Act, Babul was made a common accused. The seven organisations are Shamim Composite Mills, Jamuna Distillery, Jamuna Electronics and Engineering Industries, Jamuna Spinning Mills, Jamuna Welding and Electrode, Jamuna Knitting and Dyeing and Shamim Spinning Mills. bdnew
